    "description": "Jean Albert Laurentius Bärlin was a civil engineer born in Gävle, Sweden on September 9, 1893. He was married to Sigrid Nilsson and had four children. Bärlin graduated from Gävle high school in 1913 and from KTH (K) in 1916. He held various positions in his employment history including Materials Testing Examiner at KTH, and served on several committees and boards related to unemployment, supervisory, engineering societies and city planning. Bärlin enjoyed outdoor activities and tennis for his hobbies."
